---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { marchMadness } from '../../i18n/translations';
---

<Base translations={marchMadness}>
  <nav class="back-link">
    <a href="/" data-key="back">Back to Projects</a>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <h1 data-key="h1">Kaggle 2025 NCAA March Madness Basketball Prediction</h1>
    <p class="date" data-key="date">February 10, 2025</p>

    <h3 data-key="s_overview">Overview</h3>
    <p data-key="p_overview">Using XGBoost gradient boosting to predict NCAA men's basketball tournament outcomes based on historical team statistics and current-season rolling performance metrics. The final model ranked in the 34th percentile among 3,004 entries.</p>

    <h3 data-key="s_data">Data Sources</h3>
    <ul>
      <li data-key="li_data1"><a href="https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/march-machine-learning-mania-2025/overview" target="_blank">Kaggle Competition Data</a></li>
      <li data-key="li_data2">Time range: 2003-2024</li>
      <li data-key="li_data3">Includes all regular season and postseason scores, plus game stats such as points, rebounds, and steals</li>
    </ul>

    <img src="/images/xgboost_tree.png" alt="XGBoost Model" class="img-chart" />

    <h3 data-key="s_features">Feature Engineering</h3>
    <ul>
      <li data-key="li_feat1">Converted team statistics to differential values, reducing model parameters and increasing information density</li>
      <li data-key="li_feat2">Computed rolling averages of team performance metrics to quantify current team form</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 data-key="s_method">Model Methodology</h3>
    <ul>
      <li data-key="li_method1">Model: XGBoost</li>
      <li data-key="li_method2">Tree-based models handle non-linear relationships well and automatically select the most informative features</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 data-key="s_findings">Key Findings</h3>
    <ol>
      <li data-key="li_f1">Significant difference between regular season and postseason performance</li>
      <li data-key="li_f2">Model performs consistently across different postseason bracket structures</li>
      <li data-key="li_f3">Model favors statistically dominant teams, leading to lower accuracy when upsets occur</li>
      <li data-key="li_f4">Achieved a Brier Score of 0.19 for the current year's tournament, indicating good accuracy</li>
    </ol>

    <h3 data-key="s_future">Future Improvements</h3>
    <ol>
      <li data-key="li_fut1">Data is only collected at the team level, not player level -- granularity is limited</li>
      <li data-key="li_fut2">Tree-based models are less effective than LSTM and CNN at capturing temporal relationships in sequential data</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</Base>
